{[%evp 0,46,21,-18,16,10,10,10,11,10,18,-1,-1,-12,-4,-13,3,-2,17,17,69,69,70,42,42,-2,25,23,27,26,60,55,54,68,56,53,42,46,47,50,43,46,48,50,51,48,64,75,63]} 1. Nf3 d5 2. e3 Nf6 3. c4 e6 4. b3 c5 5. Bb2 Nc6 6. cxd5 exd5 7. Nc3 $5 d4 8. Na4 Bd7 9. Rc1 {an interesting system tried by Aronian, Black should be precise for the next few moves} b6 10. exd4 (10. Bb5 {leads to a complicated position, Where it is unclear which side has the higher chances} Nb4 $1 11. Bxd7+ Nxd7 12. O-O b5 13. exd4 bxa4 14. dxc5 Bxc5 15. Bxg7 Rg8 16. Re1+ Be7 17. Be5 $1 Nxe5 18. Nxe5 Kf8 19. Qf3 (19. Qh5 Rg7 $11) 19... Bf6 $11 {not easy for White to continue the attack, but also not easy for Black to coordinate his pieces. For this reason, engine gives the 0.00 sentence}) 10... Nxd4 11. Nxd4 cxd4 12. Bxd4 {White has an extra pawn, but his pieces are lacking of coordination, so Black should take profit of it with a fast play} Be7 (12... Bd6 $5 {better in my opinion} 13. Be2 (13. Qe2+ Be6 14. Qb5+ Bd7 $11) 13... O-O 14. O-O Bxa4 15. Bxf6 (15. bxa4 $2 Bxh2+ $15) 15... Bxb3 16. Bxd8 Bxd1 17. Rfxd1 Rfxd8 $11) 13. Bb2 O-O 14. Be2 Nd5 15. O-O Nf4 16. Bf3 Rc8 $6 (16... Bd6 $1 {best move by engine, showing that the best square was d6 and not e7}) 17. Rxc8 (17. d4 $14) 17... Bxc8 18. Qa1 f6 19. d4 Qd7 20. Bc1 Bd6 21. Bxf4 Bxf4 22. Rd1 $16 Ba6 23. g3 Bd6 24. Nc5 bxc5 25. dxc5 Be5 26. Rxd7 Bxa1 27. Rxa7 Bd3 28. a4 Re8 29. h4 Bc3 30. c6 g5 31. hxg5 fxg5 32. Rd7 Ba6 33. Bd5+ Kh8 34. c7 Ba5 35. b4 Bxb4 36. Rd8 Rf8 37. Bc4 Bc8 38. a5 Kg7 39. Rd5 h6 40. a6 Be1 41. f4 gxf4 42. a7 Bb7 43. Rd8 Bb4 44. Rxf8 Bc5+ 45. Kf1 {1-0 Aronian,L (2759)-Praggnanandhaa,R (2676) Julius Baer GenCup Prelim chess24.com INT rapid 2022 (13)} 1-0

