{[%evp 0,65,25,15,15,13,13,13,13,6,21,21,21,-8,-8,-22,-18,-18,-26,-26,-20,-16,-24,-10,-25,-25,30,39,39,17,35,35,35,60,77,79,80,76,67,70,95,104,111,107,108,98,151,131,140,114,114,101,127,115,127,117,92,103,104,107,107,62,91,91,86,86,85,64]} 1. Nf3 d5 2. e3 Nf6 3. c4 e6 4. Nc3 b6 5. cxd5 exd5 6. g3 {This system is a serious one. It was played by GM Keymer more than 20 times!} Bd6 {With White preparing to play Bg2, Black opts to postpone the development of Bb7, recognizing the potential opportunity to execute Ba6-Nc5 ideas in certain scenarios} 7. Bg2 O-O 8. O-O Re8 $1 {waiting for White's next move} (8... Ba6 {it is also possible but better to wait until White has played b3 because} 9. Re1 Nbd7 10. d4 Re8 11. Nd2 {White didn't play b3, so Black now doesn't have Bb4 ideas as Nc3 is not so vulnerable. Still the position is around equal, but maybe White can hope for something small}) 9. Re1 (9. b3 Ba6 10. Re1 Nbd7 11. d4 (11. d3 Nc5 12. Bf1 Ne6 13. Bb2 h6 14. Rc1 c5 $11) 11... Bb7 12. Bb2 (12. Nd2 Bb4 $1 13. Bb2 Ne4 $11) 12... Ne4 13. Rc1 Nxc3 14. Bxc3 a5 $5 {Black is perfectly fine}) (9. Qc2 Bb7 $1 (9... Ba6 $6 {not a good idea here as White has Rd1} 10. Rd1 $1 $14 {Zwardon-Bartel 2022}) 10. b3 c5 11. Bb2 (11. d4 Nc6 12. dxc5 bxc5 13. Rd1 Nb4 14. Qb1 d4 15. exd4 cxd4 16. Nxd4 (16. Rxd4 Qe7 $36 {White is behind in development}) 16... Bxg2 17. Kxg2 Be5 18. Nc6 Qc7 19. Nxe5 Rxe5 20. a3 Qxc3 21. axb4 Qxb4 22. Bb2 Qb7+ 23. Kg1 Re6 $11) 11... Nc6 $11) 9... Nbd7 10. d3 Ba6 11. e4 (11. Nd4 $6 {Keymer-Pichot} Ne5 $1 $15) 11... dxe4 (11... Bb7 $1 $146 12. Nh4 (12. Qc2 h6 $11 {Ne5 next}) 12... dxe4 13. dxe4 Be5 14. Qc2 Nc5 15. Rd1 Qc8 16. f3 g6 {very complicated position with equal chances}) 12. dxe4 Ne5 (12... Ng4 {would have been a better try} 13. h3 Nge5 14. Be3 Nc5 15. Nxe5 Bxe5 16. Bxc5 Qxd1 17. Raxd1 bxc5 18. Bf1 {White can hope for a symbolic enge in this endgame}) 13. Nxe5 Bxe5 14. Bf4 $1 Qd6 15. Qa4 {and White gets a stable advantage} Bb7 16. Rad1 Qc5 17. Bxe5 Rxe5 18. Qd4 Qxd4 19. Rxd4 Kf8 20. f4 Rc5 21. Re2 Ng8 22. Red2 Ke8 23. Bh3 ({I like} 23. e5 Bxg2 24. Kxg2 Ne7 25. Rd7 {Where probably White is close to be objectively winning}) 23... Bc6 24. R2d3 a5 25. a3 a4 26. Rd2 h5 27. e5 Nh6 28. Bg2 Nf5 29. Bxc6+ Rxc6 30. Re4 Rg6 31. Nb5 Rc6 32. Kf2 Rc5 33. Rb4 Rc1 34. Nc3 Rd8 35. Rxd8+ Kxd8 36. Re4 Rh1 37. Kg2 Rc1 38. Re2 Ke7 39. Nxa4 Ke6 40. Nc3 Nd4 41. Rd2 Nb3 42. Rf2 Nd4 43. Ne2 Nxe2 44. Rxe2 Rd1 45. Kh3 g6 46. Rc2 c5 47. Rc3 f6 48. Rb3 fxe5 49. Rxb6+ Kf5 50. Rc6 Rc1 51. fxe5 Rc2 52. a4 g5 53. g4+ hxg4+ 54. Kg3 Rxb2 55. e6 Rb3+ 56. Kf2 Rb2+ 57. Ke3 Kf6 58. Rxc5 1/2-1/2

